# 11. Controller

```java
package com.yourcompany.lancelot.controller;

import com.yourcompany.lancelot.dto.AppConfigResponse;
import com.yourcompany.lancelot.service.AppConfigService;
import lombok.RequiredArgsConstructor;
import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.*;

@RestController
@RequiredArgsConstructor
@RequestMapping("/apps")
public class AppController {

    private final AppConfigService appConfigService;

    @GetMapping("/{appId}")
    public AppConfigResponse getApp(@PathVariable String appId) {
        return appConfigService.getApp(appId);
    }
}
```

If you keep the context path `/lancelot`, then your full local URL becomes:

```text
http://localhost:8081/lancelot/apps/B2BOOST_BE
```

If you remove that context path, then it becomes:

```text
http://localhost:8081/apps/B2BOOST_BE
```

